rdf:Description.dcterms:title: The carbohydrate content of kappa casein
rdf:Description.dc:abstract: k-Casein which was electrophoretically (Starch gel) homogeneous was hydrolyzed with the enzyme Pronase P and the resultant hydrolyzate was fractionated by column chromatography. A fraction, rich in carbohydrate, was isolated by use of Sephadex G-25. Analysis showed that it contained at least nine different components. Another fraction was isolated by use of Sephadex G-50. Chromatographic, electrophoretic and ultracentrifugal analysis indicated that this fraction contained a single glycopeptide. The glycopeptide contained galactosamine (25.1%), galactose (22.1%) and sialic acid (16.6%), it has no N-term1nal amino acid and has serine as the C-terminal amino acid. Calculation based on the numbers of amino acid residues showed that the molecular weight of the glycopeptide was 11,300. [...]

rdf:Description.dcterms:title: Statistical analysis of computer systems
rdf:Description.dc:abstract: This study describes several methods used to analyse a changing computer system. The effects of these changes on the operating system and the overall Computing Centre are demonstrated. The results of this analysis have led to some short term improvements and also some projections of future computing power required to cope with an expanding demand in a University environment.
